Contract CO1: createTask
Operation:
creatTask(String title, String description, Priority priority,
Date completeBy)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task title is provided and correct.
  - The priority is chosen.

Postcodition:
  - A new Task object is created
  - Task attributes including title, description, priority, the completion date, the
  date it was created, and status) are all set using the (attribute modification)
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created
  - The ActivityEntry then gets associated with the Task 
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes such as timestamp and description are set

Contract C02: removeTask
Operation:
removeTask(int taskId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task that needs to be removed exists

Posconditions:
- The status of the task is changed to cancelled
- The task remains still in the system and does not get deleted
- A new ActivityEntry pbject is created 
- The ActivityEntry object is associated with the Task 
- The ActivityEntry's attributes such as timestamp and description are set 

Contract CO3: updateTask
Operation:
updateTask(...)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task that needs to be updated exists.

Postcondition:
  - One or more Task attributes (title, description, priority, due date, or status) are updated (attribute modification).
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created (object creation).
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task (association formed).
  - The ActivityEntry attributes such as timestamp and description are set (attribute modification).


Contract CO4: createProject
Operation:
createProject(String name, String description)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The project name is provided.

Postcondition:
  - A new Project object is created 
  - Project attributes such as name and description are set


Contract CO5: createSubtask
Operation:
createSubtask(int parentTaskId, String title)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The parent task exists to create a subtask.
  - The desired subtask title is provided.

Postcondition:
  - A new Subtask object is created 
  - The Subtask's attributes such as title and completion status are set 
  - The Subtask is associated with its appropriate parent Task 


Contract CO6: addTags
Operation:
addTags(int taskId, String[] tags)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task exists.
  - The provided tags are valid.

Postcondition:
- The Task is associated with one or more Tag objects.
- New Tag objects are created if they do not already exist


Contract CO7: viewActivityHistory
Operation:
viewActivityHistory(int taskId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task you want to view history for exists.

Postcondition:
  - All Activity entries related to the Task in question are retrieved.
  - The activity history of the task is displayed to the user.


Contract CO8: viewTask
Operation:
viewTask(int taskId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and running.
  - The task you want to view exists.

Postcondition:
  - All the task's information is retrieved.
  - The task details are displayed to the user.


Contract CO9: searchTask
Operation:
searchTask(String keyword)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A keyword to search the task is provided.

Postcondition:
- Any tasks matching the keyword in the title or description are retrieved.
- Search results are displayed to the user.
